A SUSPECT who was bust for allegedly shooting and killing a man will appear in court soon. The 33-year-old will appear in the Lebowakgomo Magistrates Court outside Polokwane in Limpopo. READ: PABALLO'S LOVER: MY WIFE DIDN'T KILL HER! He faces two counts of murder and one of attempted murder. The shooting happened at Mashite Village in Ga-Mphahlele outside Polokwane on Thursday. The suspect was allegedly sitting with his brothers and the deceased’s dad at Talenteng Entertainment Centre when a scuffle ensued. It was reported that the deceased his brother and another man rushed to the centre after hearing their father was being assaulted. Limpopo police spokesman Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said the suspect allegedly shot them with his licensed firearm, instantly killing Jacky Tema (26) and critically wounding his brother Reuben (46) and a 40-year-old man. READ: RAGE OVER KFC WEDDING! “It’s unfortunate that the critically wounded Ruben succumbed to his injuries in hospital on Saturday. The other victim is still recuperating in hospital,” said Mojapelo. It’s understood that a vehicle belonging to the suspect was burnt to ashes by an angry mob after the incident. Police have confiscated the firearm allegedly used in the shooting.